But Chelsea boss Mourinho said: ‘I think he loves Chelsea already. He’s so happy: the way he plays, the way he’s a member of the squad, the way he lives in this little blue village. It is like he’s here for a long time.

‘If you ask him now if he regrets the move, I’m sure he’d say no. If you ask him if he’d choose a different option, he’d say no. And if you ask him where he thinks he’ll be in five years, he’d say he sees himself here in five years. He is Chelsea.’

Despite the protracted and unsavoury manner of Fabregas’s Arsenal departure in 2011, Wenger insisted ‘he is a person I love’ and called for fans to give him a ‘respectful’ reception. 

